<body>
    <header>
        <h1><marquee height="45">Beef and Broccoli</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>1 pound flank steak, thinly sliced</li>
            <li>1/2 cup soy sauce</li>
            <li>3 tablespoons oyster sauce</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons brown sugar</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon cornstarch</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon sesame oil</li>
            <li>3 cloves garlic, minced</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon ginger, grated</li>
            <li>1 cup broccoli florets</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons vegetable oil</li>
            <li>Cooked white rice for serving</li>
            <li>Sesame seeds and sliced green onions for garnish</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>main dish</li>
            <li>Asian</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>In a bowl, mix soy sauce, oyster sauce, brown sugar, cornstarch, and sesame oil to create the marinade.</li>
            <li>Add the thinly sliced flank steak to the marinade and let it sit for at least 15 minutes.</li>
            <li>Heat vegetable oil in a wok or large skillet over medium-high heat. Add minced garlic and grated ginger, and stir-fry for about 30 seconds.</li>
            <li>Add marinated beef to the wok and cook until browned, stirring frequently.</li>
            <li>Add broccoli florets to the wok and continue stir-frying until the broccoli is tender-crisp and the beef is cooked through.</li>
            <li>Serve over cooked white rice and garnish with sesame seeds and sliced green onions.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your tasty Beef and Broccoli!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

